As a Minnesota resident and Sierra Club volunteer opposing Line 3, I was deeply disappointed by this commission’s decision.
This has been particularly true in Wisconsin, where Enbridge built a short Line 3 segment from the Minnesota border to Superior.
The crude oil in Line 3 would cause $287 billion in climate damage over three decades, according an environmental impact statement created by the Minnesota Commerce Department.
Meanwhile, in Minnesota, Line 3 is testing newly elected Democratic Governor Tim Walz’s ability to navigate difficult political waters.
